@node Introduction

2. Introduction
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
When I softkick my A1200 into kickstart 1.2/1.3 or 2.0, the
system doesn't find the harddrive. There's no scsi.device
in those kickstarts, as in kickstart 3.0. The solution for
me was to disassemble scsi.device, reassemble, put it in
DEVS: on a bootable disk, and that way get access to the hd
under an older kickstart.

I guess I shouldn't distribute the scsi.device, so I made
GetSCSI. It copies scsi.device from the kickstart, makes
some changes so that it will be compatible with kickstart
1.2 and up, and makes an executable device-file of, it to be
put in DEVS:.


@endnode
